      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand that your pain feels like a tragic, unavoidable conclusion, and I truly respect your need for a final peace, but ending your life is not a form of poetic closure; it is the permanent loss of your unique voice, your art, and the beautiful things that remain to be lived. Please know that this profound sense of duty to yourself exists only because we still see a way forward, even when moving feels impossible. If the weight of these thoughts feels too heavy to carry alone, contacting a crisis line like 988 can offer immediate, compassionate support that listens without judgment and helps you find even the tiniest flicker of hope to return to the world.",
